Emacs

* Help 
** get help 
- C-h
** get help for a single command 
- C-h c command
** display documentation for a single command 
- C-h k command
** get help for a function 
- C-h f
** get help for a variable 
- C-h v
** list all commands with keyword 
- C-h a
** view documentation of current major mode 
- C-h m
** to get pop up tool bar 
- C-right_click
* Combinations with other commands
** repeat commands 
- C-u n command;
- C-v, M-v are exceptions - screen scrolls by n lines instead of 1 screen
** stop emacs 
- C-g - stops all commands
** disabled commands 
- press <SPC> to execute when prompted
** undo 
- C-x u or C_
** all-purpose get out 
- <esc><esc><esc>
* Windows
** maximize current window 
- C-x 1
** split into windows horizontally 
-  C-x 2
** split into windows vertically 
-  C-x 3
** open file in new window and move cursor there too 
-  C-x 4 C-f
** move to next window 
-  C-x o
** make current window taller 
- C-x ^
** make current window wider 
- C-x }
** shring window horizontally 
- C-x {
** make all windows the same size 
- C-x +
** move down in the next window 
- C-M-v 
- useful when you're taking notes in one window from a document in another window
** delete current window 
- C-x 0
* Frames
** create new frame 
- C-x 5 2
** move between frames 
- C-x 5 o
** delete frame 
- C-x 5 0
* Regions
** set Mark 
- C-Spc
- then move cursor to select region
* Rectangles
** once region is selected
** copy rectangle to register
- c-x r r 
** kill rectangle
- c-x r k 
** yank rectangle
- c-x r y 
** open rectangle shifting text right
- c-x r o 
** blank out rectangle
- c-x r c 
** to add prefix each string
- c-x r t 
* Transposing
** exchanges 2 entities
** transpose characters
- c-t 
** transpose words
- m-t 
** transpose lines
- c-x c-t 
** transpose sexps
- c-m-t 
* Bookmarks
** set bookmark
- C-x r m
** jump to bookmark
- C-x r b
** list all bookmarks
- C-x r l
* Org-babel
** easy templates
- s 	#+BEGIN_SRC ... #+END_SRC
- e 	#+BEGIN_EXAMPLE ... #+END_EXAMPLE
- q 	#+BEGIN_QUOTE ... #+END_QUOTE
- v 	#+BEGIN_VERSE ... #+END_VERSE
- c 	#+BEGIN_CENTER ... #+END_CENTER
- l 	#+BEGIN_LaTeX ... #+END_LaTeX
- L 	#+LaTeX:
- h 	#+BEGIN_HTML ... #+END_HTML
- H 	#+HTML:
- a 	#+BEGIN_ASCII ... #+END_ASCII
- A 	#+ASCII:
- i 	#+INDEX: line
- I 	#+INCLUDE: line 
